William BINDER v. C. H. LOONEY, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Leavenworth, Kansas. No. 6086. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. May 26, 1959. Wilbur G. Leonard, U. S. Atty., E. Edward Johnson, Asst. U. S. Atty., Topeka, Kan., Milton P. Beach, Asst. U. S. Atty., Kansas City, Kan., and George E. Peabody, Asst. U. S. Atty., Wichita, Kan., for appellee.

Before BRATTON, Chief Judge, and PHILLIPS and LEWIS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Affirmed without written opinion, on the ground that the appeal is without merit.
